Where do I get my Lego?
- Bricklink.com, and the Lego store
How do I make my videos?

snippet.title: #7 LAKERS at #2 NUGGETS | FULL GAME 1 HIGHLIGHTS | April 20, 2024
snippet.description:
Never miss a moment with the latest news, trending stories and highlights to bring you closer to your favorite players and teams.
Download now: https://link.nba.com/NBAYouTube

The Denver Nuggets defeated the Los Angeles Lakers, 114-103. Nikola Jokic led the way for the Nuggets with 32 points, 12 rebounds, and 7 assists, while Anthony Davis tallied 32 points, 14 rebounds, 5 assists, and 4 blocks for the Lakers in the losing effort. The Nuggets lead this best-of-seven series, 1-0, with Game 2 taking place on Monday, April 22nd (10:00 p.m. ET, TNT/TruTV).

snippet.description:
We set sail for what we thought would be a leisurely 250 nm sail from Subic to the northern part of Palawan. ¬†How na√Øve!¬† Mother nature had a full mix of wind and waves in store for us.¬† It felt like we were learning how to sail all over again.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

WE‚ÄôRE JASON AND NIKKI WYNN.  A couple of explorers, modern-day documentarians, and cultivators of curiosity.

We‚Äôve been chasing our curiosity around the world on wheels and keels since 2011. Why?  Because curiosity is the key to unlocking life.  It pushes us outside our comfort zone, softens our assumptions, and helps us embrace the great unknown.  The more we let our curiosity lead the way, the more we discover about ourselves and the world around us.

Things We're Most Curious About:

GETTING OFF-GRID 
Our home is also our transportation and we spend weeks away from civilization and sometimes land.  So self-reliance and sustainable living are a must.  We've learned heaps about renewable energy, managing waste, creating safe drinking water and foraging for food.  We carefully manage our resources and we‚Äôre always looking for new and better ways to do so.  

TALKING TO STRANGERS
People are busy (even on remote islands) and travelers are a dime a dozen.  It takes time to talk to strangers, and even more time to have a real connection.  Going the extra mile to get to know someone is a commitment. 

Which is why these are our most treasured experiences.  Setting off into the world with curiosity as our guide and nature as our compass.  We talk to strangers and accept hospitality without fear or reservations.  Both giving and receiving.

ALTERNATIVE LIVING
These are people who are doing things differently. Forgoing the mainstream, seeking freedom and living on the margins. Creative, unique and inspiring people who challenge our ideas of home and community.

Our journey is ever-evolving but the mission remains the same: #CultivateCuriosity

WE‚ÄôRE JASON AND NIKKI WYNN.  A couple of explorers, modern-day documentarians, and cultivators of curiosity.

We‚Äôve been chasing our curiosity around the world on wheels and keels since 2011. Why?  Because curiosity is the key to unlocking life.  It pushes us outside our comfort zone, softens our assumptions, and helps us embrace the great unknown.  The more we let our curiosity lead the way, the more we discover about ourselves and the world around us.

Things We're Most Curious About:

GETTING OFF-GRID 
Our home is also our transportation and we spend weeks away from civilization and sometimes land.  So self-reliance and sustainable living are a must.  We've learned heaps about renewable energy, managing waste, creating safe drinking water and foraging for food.  We carefully manage our resources and we‚Äôre always looking for new and better ways to do so.  

TALKING TO STRANGERS
People are busy (even on remote islands) and travelers are a dime a dozen.  It takes time to talk to strangers, and even more time to have a real connection.  Going the extra mile to get to know someone is a commitment. 

Which is why these are our most treasured experiences.  Setting off into the world with curiosity as our guide and nature as our compass.  We talk to strangers and accept hospitality without fear or reservations.  Both giving and receiving.

ALTERNATIVE LIVING
These are people who are doing things differently. Forgoing the mainstream, seeking freedom and living on the margins. Creative, unique and inspiring people who challenge our ideas of home and community.

Our journey is ever-evolving but the mission remains the same: #CultivateCuriosity

snippet.title: Roblox The Strongest Battlegrounds In A Nutshell
snippet.description:
Get a browser that‚Äôs literally better at everything: https://operagx.gg/TankFish

Roblox The Strongest Battlegrounds is a Roblox fighting game based on the anime One Punch Man. It is a free-for-all arena fight where skill and mastery are everything. Each character has 4 normal moves, and when you deal enough damage, you can unlock your ultimate, which gives you another set of more powerful moves. 

There are currently 8 different characters in the game, with 1 work in progress and one for private servers only. Their moves are based on their anime/manga counterparts and each has different playstyles, combos and techs that players will need to learn to be pro. I will try to showcase as many good combos and tips in this video as possible.

The strongest hero is based on Saitama. You have no ranged attacks nor gap closers, so landing the first m1 will be the most difficult. After that, there are many combos and techs available to deal a ton of damage. His ultimate charges twice as fast but can only use 1 move per ultimate. 

Hero Hunter is based on Garou. He only has 3 offensive moves with a counter. However, his moves deal high damage and are easy to combo extends. The favorite character for the try hard sweaty gamers out there.

Destructive Cyborg is based on Genos. He is very versatile but can be blocked or countered very easily since the moves have a predictable delay. His ultimates have a lot of area damage, GREAT at make everyone on the map mad. 

Deadly Ninja is based on Speed-o'-Sound Sonic. He is the perfect character for kill stealing and being annoying. It‚Äôs not the most fun character to play, but it‚Äôs very unfun to play against.

Brutal Demon is based on Metal Bat. He has a lot of move variations and can adapt to many different situations. His ultimate bar charges when he takes damage, so you can have fun even if you are a noob.

Blade Master is based on Atomic Samurai. His combos are easy to start but difficult to finish. He has a very strong ultimate, so try to get good and get it ASAP.

Wild Psychic is based on Tatsumaki / Fubuki. It is currently not finished, but she‚Äôs super annoying to play against. She pulls you, pushes you and seals you under a rock. Good for teamers.

Sorcerer is based on Gojo Satoru. He is only available to the private server owner. He is invincible and one-shots everyone. 

So yeah, just like the other Roblox In A Nutshell videos, I will attempt to show everything The Strongest Battleground has to offer. Like always, this Roblox video is filled with a crapload of dumb jokes and dead memes and takes the form of funny moments/funny montage/edits. The game will have new updates in the future, and I might play it again. Hit the like and the subscribe button. If you enjoyed this video, click the bell icon and don't forget to comment.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This video contains a crap load of dead memes and bad jokes. Viewer discretion advised.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Be sure to leave a like if you enjoyed this Roblox video!
Thanks for watching!

It‚Äôs unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 8 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX ‚Äî interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything ‚Äî be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer ‚ÄúCapture the Flag‚Äù game or some other, yet¬≠to¬≠be¬≠dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (‚ÄúROBUX‚Äù). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

snippet.title: Lamborghini Revuelto v Ferrari SF90 v Porsche 918: DRAG RACE
snippet.description:
Sell your car for free with Carwow: https://bit.ly/Sell-Your-Car-For-Free-2004

Lamborghini Revuelto drag race let‚Äôs GOOO!! 

We‚Äôve finally got our hands on this all-new Lambo, and it‚Äôs facing off against two of its top rivals - the Ferrari SF90, and the Porsche 918 Spyder! So let‚Äôs check out how these three epic hypercars compare. 

Starting with the Lambo, it‚Äôs powered by a 6.5-litre naturally-aspirated V12 along with THREE electric motors! These combine to produce 1,015hp and 1,062Nm of torque. Power is sent to all four wheels via an 8-speed dual-clutch gearbox, and it weighs in at 1,772kg. If you‚Äôre looking to pick one up, it‚Äôll cost you at least ¬£447,000! 

Then we come to the SF90. It‚Äôs equipped with a 4-litre twin-turbo V8, and just like the Lambo it also has three electric motors. These combine to produce 1,000hp and 800Nm, and power is sent to all four wheels via an 8-speed automatic gearbox. It tips the scales at 1,570kg, and if you try and pick one up today it‚Äôll cost around ¬£376,000. 

Then finally we have the 918. It‚Äôs powered by a 4.6-litre naturally-aspirated V8 along with two electric motors. These work in tandem to put down 887hp and 1,280Nm of torque. It sends this power to all four wheels via a 7-speed dual-clutch gearbox, and it weighs in at 1,674kg. It‚Äôs easily the most expensive car here, as it‚Äôs now valued at an incredible 1.3 million pounds! 

So will the Lambo walk it? There‚Äôs only one way to find out‚Ä¶ LET‚ÄôS RACE!

Thanks to @wam_barn & @tomi-auto  for lending us their cars for this drag race!

snippet.title: Boosie Shows Boosie Town: 4 Homes He Built for His Kids on His 88 Acre Property (Part 1)
snippet.description:
Watch the full interview now as a VladTV Youtube Member - https://www.youtube.com/vladtv/join

--------
Part 2: https://youtu.be/x7MlGPBL6S8
Boosie has revealed that he is building homes on his 88-acre property for his kids. Boosie showed off the construction progress on four two-story homes, explaining that they were nearly completed with just a few inspections remaining. Boosie detailed his plans for the property, naming it "Gotham City" and joking about being the landlord, challenging his kids to take care of their homes. The hip-hop artist shared that he is also consulting with investors from Saudi Arabia to fund a subdivision project on his land. Beyond his aspirations for real estate, Boosie plans to install a go-kart track and a third swimming pool on the property. When asked about the cost of the properties, Boosie did not provide a figure, stating it would depend on the final additions and designs.

snippet.title: LeBron, Travis Scott, Ice Spice, Ochocinco, Sauce Gardner and J-Rod on Awards & Snubs | The Shop S7
snippet.description:
IT'S LIT! Tap back into The Shop with LeBron James, artist & CEO Travis Scott, NFL corner Sauce Gardner, music star Ice Spice, media personality and former all-pro Chad Johnson and MLB all-star Julio Rodriguez.

Maverick and PR speak to LeBron about never winning Defensive Player of the Year, the importance of a strong inner circle and why he steered away from playing football. Travis gives his thoughts on his GRAMMYs snub, his love of performing and his overall approach to creativity. Ice Spice talks about her come-up in New York City and walks the guys through her GRAMMYs experience. Sauce talks about his early success in the league, going up against the best receivers in the NFL and how he approaches his role on the field. Ocho talks about raw talent vs hard work, his strategy of trash-talk and more. Julio discusses baseball culture in the Dominican Republic and transitioning into the big leagues.

As always, we get to it!

The Shop is presented by @greygoose.

In LeBron James‚Äô words...‚ÄúEverything happens in The Shop.‚Äù The Sports Emmy Award-winning series The Shop is back for Season 7! Join us this season for new episodes featuring the biggest names in the game for unfiltered talk about sports, music, and culture.

snippet.title: Neil deGrasse Tyson Explains The Three-Body Problem
snippet.description:
What is the three body problem? Neil deGrasse Tyson and comedian Chuck Nice break down why the three body problem is unsolvable and what makes it mathematically chaotic. 

Is the solar system unstable? Find out about Isaac Newton‚Äôs worries about the solar system, Pierre-Simon Laplace‚Äôs calculus, and perturbation theory. Would a binary star system be chaotic? What about a star system with three suns? Four suns? Five? Learn about the restricted three body problem and how the Jupiter-Earth-Sun system could be chaotic down the line.

Check out our second channel, @StarTalkPlus

Get the NEW StarTalk book, 'To Infinity and Beyond: A Journey of Cosmic Discovery' on Amazon: https://amzn.to/3PL0NFn

snippet.title: 2024 Toyota Land Cruiser Review // Idiot Proof

The 2024 Toyota Land Cruiser in ‚ÄòLand Cruiser‚Äô trim ($61,950 starting in the US, $77,290 starting in Canada) is brand new and now comes standard with a hybrid four-cylinder turbo i-FORCE MAX engine. It‚Äôs good for 326 horsepower and 465 lb ft of torque, and comes with many off road goodies like a locking differential, detachable sway bars, and a 2400 watt outlet in the trunk. But where exactly does the Land Cruiser fit into Toyota‚Äôs lineup among the 4Runner and the Lexus GX? And does this new hybrid Land Cruiser live up to its reputation of reliability and capability? Thomas and James head to the Algodones Dunes to find out. We hope you enjoy the episode! And then subscribe, silly.

snippet.title: The Complete FALLOUT Timeline Explained!
snippet.description:
The Fallout franchise has a long and complex history and timeline that has been expanding its post-apocalyptic future ever since the original game‚Äôs release back in 1997. With 4 mainline games, a handful of spin-offs, and now a TV show that‚Äôs set within the same universe, the series has a big, meaty timeline to wrap your head around. And with the Amazon Prime TV show expanding on the franchise‚Äôs lore, and extending the timeline further into the future, there is no better time to dive back into the lore of Fallout than now.

This is the Fallout timeline fully explained.

From the Pre-War origins of RobCo. and Vault-Tec all the way through to Lucy MacLean‚Äôs journey to find her father via the stories set in the Capital Wasteland and the Commonwealth, this video breaks down the long and complex timeline of the Fallout franchise.

This is the Fallout timeline fully explained.

From the Pre-War origins of RobCo. and Vault-Tec all the way through to Lucy MacLean‚Äôs journey to find her father via the stories set in the Capital Wasteland and the Commonwealth, this video breaks down the long and complex timeline of the Fallout franchise.

snippet.title: LAKERS at PELICANS | #SoFiPlayIn | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | April 16, 2024
snippet.description:
Never miss a moment with the latest news, trending stories and highlights to bring you closer to your favorite players and teams.
Download now: https://link.nba.com/NBAYouTube

LeBron James (23 points, 9 rebounds, 9 assists), D‚ÄôAngelo Russell (21 points, 6 assists, 5 3pt. FG), and Anthony Davis (20 points, 15 rebounds, 3 blocks) combine for 64 points to lead the Los Angeles Lakers over the New Orleans Pelicans, 110-106, securing the No. 7 seed in the Western Conference Playoffs. Zion Williamson tallied 40 points, 11 rebounds and 5 assists for the Pelicans. 

The Lakers will face the Denver Nuggets in the first round of the 2024 NBA Playoffs with Game 1 Saturday, April 20, while the Pelicans will face the winner Warriors-Kings for a chance at the No. 8 seed Friday, April 19

Zion Williamson is the first player in Play-In history with at least 40 points, 10 rebounds and 5 assists in a game.

snippet.title: Devin Haney & Ryan Garcia Have an Epic Conversation | One on One | GQ Sports
snippet.description:
Devin Haney and Ryan Garcia face-off Saturday, April 20 in Brooklyn, New York. Originally, we planned an epic face-to-face conversation with the fighters pre-match, but tensions are so high they wouldn't sit together. Instead, we've got exclusive separate interviews with both. Who has more drip? How long have they been rivals? Why did they agree to this fight? The title-defending lightweight champion Haney and the formidable Garcia offer their predictions for this fight and share some subtle digs about their readiness and strategies.

snippet.title: DEVIN HANEY: MILLION DOLLAZ WORTH OF GAME EPISODE 269
snippet.description:
Devin Haney, a rising star in the world of boxing, returns to the Million Dollaz Worth Of Game podcast with a wealth of experiences to share. Haney‚Äôs career has been marked by determination, skill, and a relentless pursuit of excellence. His upcoming bout with Ryan Garcia on April 20, 2024, promises to be a clash of titans, and fans are eagerly awaiting this showdown.

In a recent episode, Haney took listeners on a tour of his opulent Las Vegas property, where he houses an impressive collection of cars valued at over 3 million dollars. Beyond the glitz and glamour, Haney delved into the heart of boxing. He candidly discussed how popularity, rather than pure skill, often dictates who earns the big paychecks in the sport.

But it‚Äôs Haney‚Äôs unique bond with his father that truly sets him apart. Unlike other father-son duos in boxing, their success hasn‚Äôt driven them apart; instead, it has brought them closer. Haney‚Äôs admiration for his father‚Äôs guidance and unwavering support shines through in every conversation.

Lastly, Haney shared his list of the top 5 boxers in the game today, along with his thoughts on who truly deserves a spot in the boxing Hall of Fame. His insights are a testament to his passion for the sport and his commitment to leaving a lasting legacy.

snippet.description:

AI is everywhere. Is it all it's cracked up to be or is it one big scam? Well, as it is for most things, the truth is somewhere in the middle. In this episode we see how, despite some of AI's useful contributions, the hype has also impacted the tech industry negatively.
